---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
---
<Layout
	title="Docs · flipagent"
	description="flipagent developer docs — quickstart, MCP setup, REST reference, authentication, rate limits, errors, and self-hosting guides."
>
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>Docs</h1>
				<p class="lead">
					The API to resell on eBay for AI agents. Pick how you want to call it.
				</p>

				<div class="features" style="margin:32px 0 56px;">
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="ic">i.</div>
						<h3>MCP server</h3>
						<p><code>flipagent-mcp</code> for Claude Code (and any MCP-compatible host). Every reseller endpoint exposed as an MCP tool.</p>
						<div style="margin-top:14px;"><a href="/docs/mcp/">MCP setup →</a></div>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="ic">ii.</div>
						<h3>REST API</h3>
						<p>Unified <code>/v1/*</code> surface at <code>api.flipagent.dev</code>: items (active + sold), evaluate, ship, listings, sales, purchases, payouts, transactions, categories, products.</p>
						<div style="margin-top:14px;"><a href="/docs/rest/">REST quickstart →</a></div>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="ic">iii.</div>
						<h3>TypeScript SDK</h3>
						<p><code>@flipagent/sdk</code>. One client, every namespace. Auto-typed responses, server-side scoring.</p>
						<div style="margin-top:14px;"><a href="/docs/quickstart/">Quickstart →</a></div>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="ic">iv.</div>
						<h3>Chrome extension</h3>
						<p>Powers buying and package-forwarder ops (<code>/v1/purchases</code>, <code>/v1/forwarder/*</code>) inside your real Chrome session. eBay's checkout is human-only by policy; the extension keeps every click in your hands.</p>
						<div style="margin-top:14px;"><a href="/docs/extension/">Extension setup →</a></div>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="ic">v.</div>
						<h3>Scraper</h3>
						<p><code>@flipagent/ebay-scraper</code>. Standalone eBay HTML parsers + plain-HTTPS fetcher. BYO proxy for sustained volume.</p>
						<div style="margin-top:14px;"><a href="https://github.com/flipagent/flipagent/tree/main/packages/ebay-scraper">Source →</a></div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<h2>Quickstart</h2>

				<table class="api">
					<thead>
						<tr><th>Goal</th><th>Path</th><th>Time</th></tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>Try from Claude Code</td><td><a href="/docs/mcp/">MCP setup</a></td><td>30s</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Call from your backend</td><td><a href="/docs/rest/">REST quickstart</a></td><td>1m</td></tr>
						<tr><td>TypeScript SDK</td><td><a href="/docs/quickstart/">Quickstart</a></td><td>2m</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Browse the API</td><td><a href="/docs/api/">API reference</a></td><td>any time</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h2>What you'll need</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>A free API key from <a href="/signup/">flipagent.dev/signup</a>.</li>
					<li>For sell-side endpoints (<code>/v1/listings</code>, <code>/v1/sales</code>, <code>/v1/payouts</code>, <code>/v1/policies</code>, etc.): connect your regular eBay account once at <code>/v1/connect/ebay</code>. flipagent owns the eBay developer keyset, so you do not need an eBay developer account of your own.</li>
					<li>For the buy-flow (<code>/v1/purchases</code> bridge mode): the <a href="/docs/extension/">Chrome extension</a> runs the BIN clicks inside your real Chrome session.</li>
				</ul>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
